==English==

===Noun===
'''[[moot]] [[point]]'''

# An [[issue]] that is subject to, or open for [[discussion]] or [[debate]].
#:''Now that downtown has been rebuilt and business is booming, whether to build more parking spaces has become a '''moot point'''.''
# An issue regarded as potentially debatable, but not worth debating.
#: ''Until we rebuild downtown, whether we build more parking spaces or not is a '''moot point'''.''

===Usage notes===
*The variant "mute point" appears to be based on a [[mondegreen]], and is widely considered incorrect.
*The second sense given above is regarded by some as incorrect.  For example, see [http://www.worldwidewords.org/qa/qa-moo1.htm this link].